                <p>
            <pb/>The <hi rend="italic">St Nicholas</hi>, Morgan, which has arrived off
                    <lb/>Aberdeen from Bathurst, New South Wales, reports <lb/>that timber was very
                    scarce ; that the woods between <lb/>that town and Miramichi were on fire ; that
                    250 tons <lb/>of cut timber had been burnt, and the people in the <lb/>woods had
                    been obliged to abandon their camps and <lb/>fly to save their lives. The
                    thermometer at Bathurst <lb/>was from 85 to 90.</p>
                <p/>
